A fast moving vehicle on Thursday crushed two yet- to- be identified person to death in Ayegbaju Ekiti, in Oye local government area of Ekiti state thereby causing unrest. The incident, which occurred around 2.30pm at a road bend between Ifaki and Ayegbaju Ekiti has reportedly sparked tension in the area. The victims, according to an eyewitness report were riding on a motorcycle when the vehicle which was on a high speed rammed into them and crushed them beyond recognition. The identities of the persons were unknown as of the time of filing this report. The driver of the vehicle was said to have escaped the scene of the accident and voluntarily reported himself at the nearest police station. “The driver escaped for fear of being attacked by residents. We learnt he is being detained at the police station where he went to”. Following the incident, some irate youths in the community took to the streets to protest the persistent killings of their people, through such incident, saying it is gradually becoming unbearable. They said, “The community had lost so many loved ones to accidents along the route which were as a result of recklessness of motorists”. To show their grievances, the people barricaded the major roads within the community, which halted the free flow of traffic , thereby  subjecting motorists to hardship. When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer, Ekiti Command, Mr. Sunday Abutu, who confirmed the incident said the victims had been confirmed dead at the hospital. He added that the suspect is being detained at the state police headquarters in Ado Ekiti. Abutu stated that the police had been able to calm down the rampaging youths, who were protesting incessant killing of their people in recent time. “The two victims died after they were overran by the vehicle driven by a university student. Though, there was protest but we have been able to bring it under control”, he said. 